{
    "esm": "0.4.0",
    "metadata": {
        "name": "WetScavengingLimitations",
        "description": "Combined air refreshing and cloud ice uptake limitations on wet scavenging from Luo & Yu (2023). This component unifies the two novel parameterizations of the paper into a single algebraic system: (1) the air refreshing limitation (Section 2.1, Eqs. 2/5/10/11), which reduces the wet-scavenging removal rate R_A when subgrid cloud-free (rain-free) air mixes into cloudy (rainy) air slower than the model time step; and (2) the cloud ice uptake limitation (Section 2.2, Eqs. 12-15), which limits the cold-cloud rainout efficiency F_I by the rate R_U at which water-soluble aerosols are captured by ice crystals -- the HNO3 ice uptake rate of Jacob (2000), with the temperature-dependent uptake efficiency gamma of Hudson et al. (2002). Migrated from AtmosphericDeposition.jl@e4468c79 src/luo2023.jl:326 (`WetScavengingLimitations` @component). The upstream component is a flat MTK System that inlines the equations of both AirRefreshingLimitation and CloudIceUptakeLimitation -- it does not `couple` them -- so this migration is the union of air_refreshing.esm (esm-1i3m) and cloud_ice_uptake.esm (esm-3hh9): 13 input parameters, 9 module constants, and 7 algebraic state variables (Kᵢ, τ_A, R_A, gamma, R_U, R_AU, F_I) fixed by 7 explicit equations. Observed-only: every equation is algebraic, so the 7 outputs are the algebraic solution while the ice/turbulence/grid/temperature inputs and module constants are parameters.",
        "tags": [
            "atmospheric_deposition",
            "luo2023",
            "wet-scavenging",
            "cloud-ice",
            "observed-only"
        ],
        "created": "2026-05-17T00:00:00Z",
        "authors": [
            "AtmosphericDeposition.jl contributors",
            "EarthSciModels migration (esm-s6g4)"
        ],
        "references": [
            {
                "citation": "Luo, G., & Yu, F. (2023). Impact of air refreshing and cloud ice uptake limitations on vertical profiles and wet depositions of nitrate, ammonium, and sulfate. Geophysical Research Letters, 50, e2023GL104258. https://doi.org/10.1029/2023GL104258. Eqs. 2/5/10/11 define the air refreshing limitation and Eqs. 12-15 the cloud ice uptake limitation; the cloud ice uptake rate (Eq. 14) is taken from Jacob (2000) and the HNO3-on-ice uptake efficiency (Eq. 15) from Hudson et al. (2002), as cited therein."
            },
            {
                "citation": "Jacob, D. J. (2000). Heterogeneous chemistry and tropospheric ozone. Atmospheric Environment, 34(12-14), 2131-2159. Source of the kinetic ice uptake rate R_U (Luo & Yu 2023, Eq. 14)."
            }
        ]
    },
    "models": {
        "WetScavengingLimitations": {
            "reference": {
                "notes": "source_ref: AtmosphericDeposition.jl@e4468c79c8dd4aae88646cd16d6bcf290874742c:src/luo2023.jl:326\nUpstream `WetScavengingLimitations` is an MTK `@component` that returns a flat `System(eqs, t; name)` -- it inlines the equations of both `AirRefreshingLimitation` (luo2023.jl:210) and `CloudIceUptakeLimitation` (luo2023.jl:260) directly rather than composing them as subsystems. It does NOT call `couple`/`compose`; the `coupling.couple` entry in the migration-tracker `features` column for this row does not reflect the source (the source defines a single flat system, and the only `couple` calls in AtmosphericDeposition.jl are in connector_test.jl on unrelated SuperFast/DryDeposition/WetDeposition components). This migration therefore reproduces the flat system: it is the union of the sibling air_refreshing.esm (esm-1i3m) and cloud_ice_uptake.esm (esm-3hh9) migrations -- 13 input `@parameters` (f, Rᵢ, TKE, Δx, Δy, Δz, Δt, N_I, S_I, r_ice, D_g, M, T), 9 module-level `@constants`, and 7 output `@variables` (Kᵢ, τ_A, R_A, γ, R_U, R_AU, F_I) related by 7 algebraic equations.\n\nThe 7 equations inline the upstream module-level helper functions verbatim, in the upstream source order, which is already a valid topological order (Kᵢ before τ_A; τ_A before R_A; γ before R_U; R_U and Kᵢ before R_AU; R_AU before F_I):\n  - Kᵢ ~ sqrt(2/3*TKE) * (1/(sqrt(f)*Δx) + 1/(sqrt(f)*Δy) + 1/Δz)                              (Eq. 11, cloudy_air_refreshing_rate, with the Eq. 10 turbulence velocity sqrt(2/3*TKE) inlined)\n  - τ_A ~ (1 - f)/(f*Kᵢ)                                                                        (Eq. 5, grid_refreshing_time)\n  - R_A ~ 1/(1/(f*Rᵢ) + τ_A)                                                                    (Eq. 2, air_refreshing_limited_rate)\n  - γ ~ γ_base + γ_delta*max(zero_dimless, min(one_dimless, (T_upper_luo - T)/(T_upper_luo - T_lower_luo)))   (Eq. 15, hno3_uptake_efficiency; Hudson et al. 2002)\n  - R_U ~ N_I*S_I / (r_ice/D_g + kinetic_prefactor_si*sqrt(M/M_ref)/(γ*sqrt(T/T_ref)))           (Eq. 14, cloud_ice_uptake_rate; Jacob 2000)\n  - R_AU ~ f*R_U*Kᵢ / (Kᵢ + (1-f)*R_U)                                                          (Eq. 13, air_refreshing_limited_ice_uptake_rate)\n  - F_I ~ 1 - exp(-R_AU*Δt)                                                                     (Eq. 12, cold_cloud_rainout_efficiency)\nThe rational 2/3 inside the turbulence-velocity square root is kept exact as a division of integer literals, mirroring the upstream `2 // 3`; all other integer literals (the `1`s in the reciprocals and the `1 - f` / `1 - exp` terms) likewise mirror the upstream `Int` literals.\n\nThe 9 upstream module-level `@constants` (T_upper_luo, T_lower_luo, γ_base, γ_delta, zero_dimless, one_dimless, kinetic_prefactor_si, M_ref, T_ref) are migrated as fixed-default `type: parameter` entries holding their evaluated numeric values, per the rig convention for translating MTK `@constants` (matches the sibling cloud_ice_uptake.esm migration). zero_dimless = 0.0 and one_dimless = 1.0 are the dimensionless 0/1 the Eq. 15 max/min clamp uses; they are kept as parameters rather than inlined as literals so the equation tree mirrors the upstream `hno3_uptake_efficiency` helper exactly. M_ref = 1.0 kg/mol and T_ref = 1.0 K non-dimensionalize M and T before the square roots (the upstream device for avoiding fractional unit powers); since both equal 1.0 they leave the numeric result unchanged but the structure is preserved.\n\nThe 13 input `@parameters` carry no defaults upstream (they are driven by a parent system); standalone defaults are assigned here for a representative cold-cloud GEOS-Chem-grid scenario, identical to the cloud_ice_uptake.esm sibling for every shared parameter (f=0.25, TKE=1.5 m^2/s^2, Δx=Δy=200 km, Δz=1 km, Δt=600 s, N_I=1e6 m^-3, S_I=1e-8 m^2, r_ice=1e-4 m, D_g=1e-5 m^2/s, M=0.063 kg/mol HNO3, T=210 K) plus Rᵢ=0.001 s^-1 from the air_refreshing.esm sibling. Because the combined defaults coincide with the cloud_ice_uptake.esm defaults on every cloud-ice parameter, and no cloud-ice output depends on Rᵢ, the cloud-ice test anchors (γ/R_U/Kᵢ/R_AU/F_I) carry over from cloud_ice_uptake.esm unchanged; the air-refreshing tests each pin all six air-refreshing parameters (f, Rᵢ, TKE, Δx, Δy, Δz) explicitly, so the Kᵢ/τ_A/R_A anchors carry over from air_refreshing.esm unchanged.\n\n`system_kind` is left unset (zero differential states -- no D operator), consistent with the observed-only siblings air_refreshing.esm / cloud_ice_uptake.esm.\n\nTolerance rationale (model-level rel=1e-9, abs=1e-12): observed-only algebraic system (no ODE integration). The 7 equations form a triangular chain of +, -, *, /, sqrt, exp, max, min on float64, evaluated by topological substitution; round-off is ~1e-15 per op, so rel=1e-9 leaves comfortable headroom across the value range (γ ~ 3e-3 to 7e-3, rates ~ 1e-9 to 1e1 s^-1). abs=1e-12 gates the rainout_weak_uptake F_I ~ 1.2e-7 floor case, where a pure relative tolerance would be sub-ULP."
            },
            "tolerance": {
                "rel": 1.0e-9,
                "abs": 1.0e-12
            },
            "variables": {
                "f": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.25,
                    "description": "Cloud or rainfall fraction (dimensionless)"
                },
                "Rᵢ": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "s^-1",
                    "default": 0.001,
                    "description": "In-cloud or under-rain removing rate"
                },
                "TKE": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^2/s^2",
                    "default": 1.5,
                    "description": "Turbulence kinetic energy"
                },
                "Δx": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 200000.0,
                    "description": "Grid spacing in x direction"
                },
                "Δy": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 200000.0,
                    "description": "Grid spacing in y direction"
                },
                "Δz": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 1000.0,
                    "description": "Grid spacing in z direction"
                },
                "Δt": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "s",
                    "default": 600.0,
                    "description": "Time step"
                },
                "N_I": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^-3",
                    "default": 1.0e6,
                    "description": "Ice crystal number concentration"
                },
                "S_I": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^2",
                    "default": 1.0e-8,
                    "description": "Ice crystal surface area"
                },
                "r_ice": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 1.0e-4,
                    "description": "Ice crystal radius"
                },
                "D_g": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^2/s",
                    "default": 1.0e-5,
                    "description": "Gas-phase diffusion coefficient"
                },
                "M": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "kg/mol",
                    "default": 0.063,
                    "description": "Molar mass (default: HNO3, 0.063 kg/mol)"
                },
                "T": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 210.0,
                    "description": "Temperature"
                },
                "T_upper_luo": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 220.0,
                    "description": "Upper temperature threshold for gamma (Eq. 15)"
                },
                "T_lower_luo": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 209.0,
                    "description": "Lower temperature threshold for gamma (Eq. 15)"
                },
                "γ_base": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 3.0e-3,
                    "description": "Base uptake efficiency (Eq. 15) (dimensionless)"
                },
                "γ_delta": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 4.0e-3,
                    "description": "Temperature-dependent uptake coefficient (Eq. 15) (dimensionless)"
                },
                "zero_dimless": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Zero (dimensionless) -- lower clamp of the Eq. 15 max/min"
                },
                "one_dimless": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 1.0,
                    "description": "One (dimensionless) -- upper clamp of the Eq. 15 max/min"
                },
                "kinetic_prefactor_si": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "s/m",
                    "default": 0.86933051443,
                    "description": "Kinetic theory prefactor 4*sqrt(pi/(8R)) for ice uptake in SI (Eq. 14), R = 8.314 J/(mol*K)"
                },
                "M_ref": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "kg/mol",
                    "default": 1.0,
                    "description": "Reference molar mass for non-dimensionalization of the square root"
                },
                "T_ref": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 1.0,
                    "description": "Reference temperature for non-dimensionalization of the square root"
                },
                "Kᵢ": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "s^-1",
                    "description": "Cloudy/rainy air refreshing rate (Eq. 11)"
                },
                "τ_A": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "s",
                    "description": "Grid refreshing time (Eq. 5)"
                },
                "R_A": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "s^-1",
                    "description": "Air refreshing limited removal rate (Eq. 2)"
                },
                "γ": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Uptake efficiency of HNO3 on ice (Eq. 15) (dimensionless)"
                },
                "R_U": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "s^-1",
                    "description": "Cloud ice uptake rate (Eq. 14)"
                },
                "R_AU": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "s^-1",
                    "description": "Air refreshing limited cloud ice uptake rate (Eq. 13)"
                },
                "F_I": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Cold cloud rainout efficiency (Eq. 12) (dimensionless)"
                }
            },
            "equations": [
                {
                    "_comment": "Eq. 11 - Cloudy/rainy air refreshing rate: Kᵢ = sqrt(2/3*TKE) * [1/(sqrt(f)*Δx) + 1/(sqrt(f)*Δy) + 1/Δz]. The sqrt(2/3*TKE) factor is the isotropic turbulence velocity (Eq. 10, after Stull 1988 / Pinto 1998).",
                    "lhs": "Kᵢ",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "*",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "sqrt",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "*",
                                        "args": [
                                            { "op": "/", "args": [2, 3] },
                                            "TKE"
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "+",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "/",
                                        "args": [
                                            1,
                                            {
                                                "op": "*",
                                                "args": [
                                                    { "op": "sqrt", "args": ["f"] },
                                                    "Δx"
                                                ]
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "op": "/",
                                        "args": [
                                            1,
                                            {
                                                "op": "*",
                                                "args": [
                                                    { "op": "sqrt", "args": ["f"] },
                                                    "Δy"
                                                ]
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "op": "/",
                                        "args": [1, "Δz"]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "_comment": "Eq. 5 - Grid refreshing time: τ_A = (1 - f)/(f*Kᵢ).",
                    "lhs": "τ_A",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
                            { "op": "-", "args": [1, "f"] },
                            { "op": "*", "args": ["f", "Kᵢ"] }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "_comment": "Eq. 2 - Air refreshing limited removal rate: R_A = 1/(1/(f*Rᵢ) + τ_A). As τ_A -> 0 (strong mixing) R_A -> f*Rᵢ; as τ_A -> infinity (no mixing) R_A -> 0.",
                    "lhs": "R_A",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
                            1,
                            {
                                "op": "+",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "/",
                                        "args": [
                                            1,
                                            { "op": "*", "args": ["f", "Rᵢ"] }
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    "τ_A"
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "_comment": "Eq. 15 - HNO3-on-ice uptake efficiency (Hudson et al. 2002): γ = γ_base + γ_delta*max(0, min(1, (T_upper_luo - T)/(T_upper_luo - T_lower_luo))). γ = 0.003 for T >= 220 K and γ = 0.007 for T <= 209 K, ramping linearly between.",
                    "lhs": "γ",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "+",
                        "args": [
                            "γ_base",
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    "γ_delta",
                                    {
                                        "op": "max",
                                        "args": [
                                            "zero_dimless",
                                            {
                                                "op": "min",
                                                "args": [
                                                    "one_dimless",
                                                    {
                                                        "op": "/",
                                                        "args": [
                                                            { "op": "-", "args": ["T_upper_luo", "T"] },
                                                            { "op": "-", "args": ["T_upper_luo", "T_lower_luo"] }
                                                        ]
                                                    }
                                                ]
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "_comment": "Eq. 14 - Cloud ice uptake rate (Jacob 2000): R_U = N_I*S_I / (r_ice/D_g + kinetic_prefactor_si*sqrt(M/M_ref)/(γ*sqrt(T/T_ref))). M and T are non-dimensionalized by M_ref/T_ref before the square roots to avoid fractional unit powers.",
                    "lhs": "R_U",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
                            { "op": "*", "args": ["N_I", "S_I"] },
                            {
                                "op": "+",
                                "args": [
                                    { "op": "/", "args": ["r_ice", "D_g"] },
                                    {
                                        "op": "/",
                                        "args": [
                                            {
                                                "op": "*",
                                                "args": [
                                                    "kinetic_prefactor_si",
                                                    { "op": "sqrt", "args": [ { "op": "/", "args": ["M", "M_ref"] } ] }
                                                ]
                                            },
                                            {
                                                "op": "*",
                                                "args": [
                                                    "γ",
                                                    { "op": "sqrt", "args": [ { "op": "/", "args": ["T", "T_ref"] } ] }
                                                ]
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "_comment": "Eq. 13 - Air refreshing limited cloud ice uptake rate: R_AU = f*R_U*Kᵢ / (Kᵢ + (1-f)*R_U) -- the Eq. 2 refreshing-limit structure applied to the ice uptake rate R_U.",
                    "lhs": "R_AU",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    { "op": "*", "args": ["f", "R_U"] },
                                    "Kᵢ"
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "+",
                                "args": [
                                    "Kᵢ",
                                    { "op": "*", "args": [ { "op": "-", "args": [1, "f"] }, "R_U" ] }
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "_comment": "Eq. 12 - Cold cloud rainout efficiency: F_I = 1 - exp(-R_AU*Δt). F_I is the fraction of water-soluble aerosols removed via cloud-ice uptake over a time step.",
                    "lhs": "F_I",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "-",
                        "args": [
                            1,
                            {
                                "op": "exp",
                                "args": [
                                    { "op": "-", "args": [ { "op": "*", "args": ["R_AU", "Δt"] } ] }
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                }
            ],
            "tests": [
                {
                    "id": "default_scenario",
                    "description": "Default representative cold-cloud GEOS-Chem-grid scenario at the component defaults (f = 0.25, Rᵢ = 1e-3 s^-1, TKE = 1.5 m^2/s^2, 200 km x 1 km grid, Δt = 600 s, HNO3 ice uptake at T = 210 K). Pins all seven outputs and re-checks R_A, γ, F_I at t = 1 to confirm the algebraic system is time-invariant. The air-refreshing outputs (Kᵢ/τ_A/R_A) reproduce the air_refreshing.esm `eq11_reference` anchor (which used the same f/Rᵢ/TKE/grid), and the cloud-ice outputs (γ/R_U/Kᵢ/R_AU/F_I) reproduce the cloud_ice_uptake.esm `default_cold_cloud` anchor.",
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "Kᵢ", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.00102 },
                        { "variable": "τ_A", "time": 0.0, "expected": 2941.176470588235 },
                        { "variable": "R_A", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.00014406779661016949 },
                        { "variable": "γ", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.006636363636363636 },
                        { "variable": "R_U", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0008150689881718272 },
                        { "variable": "R_AU", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.00012740904195932977 },
                        { "variable": "F_I", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.07359652878399103 },
                        { "variable": "R_A", "time": 1.0, "expected": 0.00014406779661016949 },
                        { "variable": "γ", "time": 1.0, "expected": 0.006636363636363636 },
                        { "variable": "F_I", "time": 1.0, "expected": 0.07359652878399103 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "geoschem_default",
                    "description": "Air refreshing limitation at a representative GEOS-Chem case (air_refreshing.esm `geoschem_default` anchor): f = 0.3, Rᵢ = 1e-3 s^-1, TKE = 1 m^2/s^2 on the 200 km / 1 km grid. R_A is roughly half of f*Rᵢ -- the regime where the air refreshing limitation matters most.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "f": 0.3,
                        "Rᵢ": 0.001,
                        "TKE": 1.0,
                        "Δx": 200000.0,
                        "Δy": 200000.0,
                        "Δz": 1000.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "Kᵢ", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0008314037007777247 },
                        { "variable": "τ_A", "time": 0.0, "expected": 2806.498613309816 },
                        { "variable": "R_A", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0001628709073294316 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "strong_mixing",
                    "description": "Strong-mixing limit of the air refreshing limitation (Luo & Yu 2023 limiting-behavior test): a very large TKE = 1000 m^2/s^2 on a fine 50 km / 500 m grid drives the grid refreshing time τ_A toward zero, so R_A approaches the standard well-mixed rate f*Rᵢ = 3e-4 s^-1 (here within ~1.3%).",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "f": 0.3,
                        "Rᵢ": 0.001,
                        "TKE": 1000.0,
                        "Δx": 50000.0,
                        "Δy": 50000.0,
                        "Δz": 500.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "Kᵢ", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.05352539603259635 },
                        { "variable": "τ_A", "time": 0.0, "expected": 43.59301390151994 },
                        { "variable": "R_A", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0002961272758639925 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "weak_mixing",
                    "description": "Weak-mixing limit of the air refreshing limitation (Luo & Yu 2023 limiting-behavior test): a near-zero TKE = 1e-6 m^2/s^2 on a coarse 200 km grid makes τ_A enormous, so R_A collapses to far below f*Rᵢ (R_A/(f*Rᵢ) ~ 0.0012).",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "f": 0.3,
                        "Rᵢ": 0.001,
                        "TKE": 1.0e-6,
                        "Δx": 200000.0,
                        "Δy": 200000.0,
                        "Δz": 1000.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "Kᵢ", "time": 0.0, "expected": 8.314037007777246e-07 },
                        { "variable": "τ_A", "time": 0.0, "expected": 2806498.613309816 },
                        { "variable": "R_A", "time": 0.0, "expected": 3.558931704775726e-07 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "full_cloud_coverage",
                    "description": "Full-cloud-coverage limit of the air refreshing limitation (Luo & Yu 2023 limiting-behavior test): as f -> 1 the grid refreshing time τ_A = (1-f)/(f*Kᵢ) -> 0, so R_A -> Rᵢ. At f = 0.999, R_A = 9.978e-4 s^-1, within ~0.2% of Rᵢ = 1e-3 s^-1.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "f": 0.999,
                        "Rᵢ": 0.001,
                        "TKE": 1.0,
                        "Δx": 200000.0,
                        "Δy": 200000.0,
                        "Δz": 1000.0
                    },
